article_title: Farm Tractor Crash Kills Area Man
article_text:
A Grand Ridge man is dead after his car crashed into the read of a farm tractor on Jackson County Highway 69A, Shady Grove Road south of Harmonica Rd.

The Florida Highway Patrol says Bradley D. Williams crashed into the rear of a farm tractor traveling in the southbound lane and on the south bound shoulder.

He died at the scene.

The tractor driver, 49 year old Douglas Wayne Jackson of Grand Ridge was not injured.

Troopers say Jackson’s tractor was totaled.
